response: "Why is everyone else so put together and I can't seem to get it right?"
"I feel like I'm constantly failing and never meeting society's expectations."
"I can't keep up with all the trends, it's exhausting trying to be perfect all the time."
"I feel like I'm not enough, no matter how much I try to improve myself."
"Sometimes I wonder if it's all worth it, trying to be someone I'm not."
"I'm so tired of comparing myself to others, it's driving me crazy."
"I wish I could just be content with who I am and not feel like I have to be perfect."
"Why does society put so much pressure on women to be perfect? It's not fair."
"I feel like I'm losing myself trying to fit into society's mold."
"I don't understand why I can't just be happy with myself and my own accomplishments."
